T11/25 tandem Van de Graaff accelerator.
The target was composed of a 110-mug/cm**2 C-13 layer,
98.9% isotopic purity, evaporated onto a 100-mg/cm**2
Au backing. The backing ensured complete stopping of
the beam in the target and was necessary both for
effective beam-current monitoring and for reducing the
large gamma-ray Doppler broadening.
